Uses of Package
datavisualizer.views

  • Classes in datavisualizer.views used by datavisualizer.views 
    Class and Description
    BinaryParser
    Parses a binary file, extracts states and stores a mapping of task-id to a list of (time, state)-tuples.
    InputSelection
    This class contains elements which were factored out from the ControlView class to improve structuring.
    Model
    The model unites all parts of the application.
    ProcessStateGraph
    This class represents a view containing the State Graph.
    ProcessTable
    The Process table creates the process table used in the user interface and defines its behaviour.
    StateInfo
    Represents a state (point in the graph) identified by timestamp and state.
    TaskInfo
    Represents a task as read from the xml file with all its properties (id, priority, core, name).
    TraceInfo
    This class represents a trace in the xyGraph.
    XmlParser
    This class is used to parse XML Files and extract the information for each process of each CPU core.
